Supporters of Operation Dudula sing and chant outside the Roodepoort Magistrate's Court where their leader Nhlanhla “Lux” Dlamini (not pictured) was meant to appear on March 25, 2022. JOHANNESBURG - Operation Dudula members clashed with police outside the Johannesburg Central Police Station on Friday afternoon. The leader of Operation Dudula Nhlanhla Lux Dlamini will spend the weekend behind bars. READ: Operation Dudula leader Nhlanhla Lux to remain in custody Dlamini was expected to appear in court following his arrest on Thursday. He has been at the forefront of protests against undocumented foreign nationals.  [ON AIR] Operation Dudula members clash with police outside the Johannesburg Central Police Station. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/3dszR8JydI